 Decomposition of the Problem

The retail system will be divided into several **independent functional modules**. Each module handles a specific part of the system and communicates with the others through shared databases.

This decomposition makes the system:

- easier to develop
- easier to test
- easier to maintain
- easier for multiple developers to work on.

---

 1. Customer Account Management

This module handles **customer authentication and account data**.

Functions include:

- customer registration
- login authentication
- password validation
- profile management
- loyalty point tracking

**Input**

- email
- password
- personal details

**Process**

- verify credentials
- validate user data
- store account details

**Output**

- successful login
- account creation confirmation
- updated profile

This module interacts with the **Customer Database**.

---

# 2. Product Catalogue Management

This module manages **all products available in the store**.

Functions include:

- product search
- product filtering
- product availability display
- price display

**Input**

- search terms
- category selection

**Process**

- retrieve product data from database
- filter results

**Output**

- product listings
- availability status

This module connects to the **Product Database**.

---

# 3. Order and Checkout Processing

This module manages **customer purchases**.

Functions include:

- shopping cart management
- checkout processing
- payment confirmation
- order storage

**Input**

- selected products
- quantity
- payment information

**Process**

- check stock availability
- calculate order total
- apply loyalty discounts
- store order

**Output**

- order confirmation
- updated stock levels

This module interacts with:

- Product Database
- Orders Database

---

# 4. Stock Management System

This module manages **inventory levels and product availability**.

Functions include:

- stock level monitoring
- expiry date tracking
- restock alerts

**Input**

- sales data
- delivery updates

**Process**

- update stock quantity
- identify low stock items
- detect expiring products

**Output**

- stock alerts
- restock requests

This module interacts with the **Inventory Database**.

---

# 5. Supplier Management System

This module manages communication between the shop and suppliers.

Functions include:

- sending restock requests
- receiving shipment confirmations
- delivery tracking

**Input**

- low stock alerts
- supplier updates

**Process**

- generate restock requests
- update delivery status

**Output**

- restocking orders
- delivery tracking information

This module interacts with the **Supplier Database**.

---

# 6. Admin Analytics Dashboard

This module provides **business insights to administrators**.

Functions include:

- sales analytics
- stock performance tracking
- product demand analysis
- expiry alerts

**Input**

- sales records
- stock data

**Process**

- aggregate sales information
- analyse trends

**Output**

- performance graphs
- stock reports
- business insights

This module helps management **make strategic decisions**.

---

# 7. Accessibility and User Interface System

This module ensures the system is usable by a wide range of users.

Features include:

- responsive mobile design
- adjustable text size
- high contrast mode
- screen reader compatibility

This improves **usability and accessibility for customers**.

---

# Frontend vs Backend Decomposition

The system can also be decomposed into two major layers.

### Frontend (GUI)

Handles user interaction:

- login pages
- product browsing
- checkout interface
- admin dashboard

### Backend

Handles system logic:

- authentication
- order processing
- stock management
- supplier communication
- database operations

---

# Why Decomposition Is Important

Breaking the system into modules allows:

- developers to work on **different components simultaneously**
- easier **debugging and testing**
- better **system scalability**
- clearer **developer handover documentation**




| Section | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| Visual Design | Interface layout |
| Algorithms | System logic |
| Data Requirements | Database design |
| Test Strategy | Validation plan |
| Design Documentation | Explanation for developers |

