# 2. Algorithm Designs (Logic)

These explain **how important processes work**.

---

## Algorithm 1 — Customer Login

Step-by-step logic:

```
START

User enters email and password

System checks Customer Database

IF email does not exist
    Display "Account not found"
ELSE
    IF password incorrect
        Display "Incorrect password"
    ELSE
        Login successful
        Open customer dashboard
END
```

---

## Algorithm 2 — Create Account

```
START

User enters name, email, password

Check if email already exists

IF email exists
    Display error message
ELSE
    Validate password strength

    IF password weak
        Request stronger password
    ELSE
        Save user details to database
        Account created
END
```

---

## Algorithm 3 — Product Purchase

```
START

Customer selects product
Add product to cart

Customer proceeds to checkout

Check product stock

IF stock = 0
    Display "Out of stock"
ELSE
    Calculate total price
    Apply loyalty discount

    Process payment

    IF payment fails
        Display payment error
    ELSE
        Update stock quantity
        Add loyalty points
        Save order record
END
```

---

## Algorithm 4 — Automatic Restocking

```
START

System checks stock levels

IF stock below threshold
    Generate restock request

Send request to supplier

Supplier confirms shipment

Staff track delivery location

When stock arrives
    Update inventory
END
```

---

## Flowchart 1 — Customer Login

```
START
↓
User enters email and password
↓
System searches customer database
↓
Email found?

NO → Display "Account not found"
      Return to login

YES
↓
